Boil a half-full #kettle{}. Pour it into a #saucepan with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Boil the @Basmati Rice{150%g}, ~{10-12%minutes}. Once cooked, drain, pop back in the pan and cover.

Meanwhile, heat a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, fry the @British Pork Mince{240%g}, ~{5-6%minutes}. Break up the mince as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the
> middle.

Meanwhile, grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{30%g}.

In a #bowl, mix together the @Burger Sauce{45%g} and @Coleslaw Mix{120%g}. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

Drain the fat from the mince. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add the @Tomato Puree{30%g}, @Central American Style Spice Mix{1%sachet}, @Chicken Stock Paste{10%g}
and @Water{100%ml}.

Fry until the sauce has thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove from the heat and stir in the
@Tomato Ketchup{2%tbsp}.

Add a splash of water if it's too thick. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Share your rice between #bowls{}.

Top with the spiced pork mince and slaw.

Sprinkle the cheese and @Crispy Onions{1%sachet} all over.

Enjoy!